'''Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University''' (or simply '''JRHU''') ({{lang-sa|<U+091C><U+0917><U+0926><U+094D><U+0917><U+0941><U+0930><U+0941><U+0930><U+093E><U+092E><U+092D><U+0926><U+094D><U+0930><U+093E><U+091A><U+093E><U+0930><U+094D><U+092F><U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0919><U+094D><U+0917><U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F><U+0903>}}, {{lang-hi|<U+091C><U+0917><U+0926><U+094D><U+0917><U+0941><U+0930><U+0941> <U+0930><U+093E><U+092E><U+092D><U+0926><U+094D><U+0930><U+093E><U+091A><U+093E><U+0930><U+094D><U+092F> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0902><U+0917> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F>}}), is  university located in [[Chitrakoot]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref name="about-jrhu">{{cite web | title = About JRHU | url = http://www.jrhu.com/index_files/Page329.htm | accessdate = July 21, 2009 | publisher=Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | language=Hindi | last=Shubhra | title=<U+091C><U+0917><U+0926><U+094D><U+0917><U+0941><U+0930><U+0941> <U+0930><U+093E><U+092E><U+092D><U+0926><U+094D><U+0930><U+093E><U+091A><U+093E><U+0930><U+094D><U+092F> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0902><U+0917> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F> | trans_title=Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University | url = http://www.bhartiyapaksha.com/?p=9111 | publisher=Bh<U+0101>rat<U+012B>ya Pak<U+1E63>a | accessdate = April 25, 2011 | date=February 12, 2010}}</ref> This is the first university exclusively for the disabled in India and the world.<ref>{{cite news | publisher=Hindustan Times | first=Tarun | last=Subhash | title = A Special University for Special Students: UP does a first&nbsp;<U+2013> it establishes the country's first exclusive university for physically and mentally disabled students | url = http://www.disabilityindia.org/djinstjuly05C.cfm#up | date = July 3, 2005 | accessdate = June 23, 2011}}</ref><ref name="jansatta">{{cite news | publisher=Jansatta Express | language=Hindi | first=Ragini | last=Dikshit | title= <U+091A><U+093F><U+0924><U+094D><U+0930><U+0915><U+0942><U+091F>: <U+0926><U+0941><U+0928><U+093F><U+092F><U+093E> <U+0915><U+093E> <U+092A><U+094D><U+0930><U+0925><U+092E> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0902><U+0917> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F> | trans_title = Chitrakuta: The world's first handicapped university | date = July 10, 2007}}</ref> It was established on September 27, 2001 by [[Jagadguru Rambhadracharya]], and is run by a trust named ''Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Viklang Shikshan Sansthan'', which is responsible for implementation of all the plans.<ref name="ngoboards">{{cite web |url= http://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&source=web&cd=2&sqi=2&ved=0CCQQFjAB&url=http%3A%2F%2Fngoboards.org%2Fsites%2Fngoboards.org%2Ffiles%2Fabout%2520viklang%2520seva%2520sangh.doc&ei=zn9bTtC7OI3JrAe74InHCg&usg=AFQjCNG-mthTv77vHD83gAOGkmG-rqDxJg&sig2=tngsJhF4NNRNDDOkZafquA|title= JAGADGURU RAMBHADRACHARYA VIKLANG SEVA SANGH|format= DOC|accessdate= August 29, 2011}}</ref><ref name="jrhu-education">{{cite web |url= http://jrhu.8m.net/catalog.html|title= Education|publisher= jrhu.8m.net|accessdate= August 25, 2011}}</ref> The university was created by an ordinance by the Uttar Pradesh Government, which was later passed as the Uttar Pradesh State Act&nbsp;32&nbsp;(2001) by the Uttar Pradesh legislature.<ref>{{cite web | last=Government of Uttar Pradesh | title=<U+0938><U+0942><U+091A><U+0928><U+093E> <U+0915><U+093E> <U+0905><U+0927><U+093F><U+0915><U+093E><U+0930> <U+0905><U+0927><U+093F><U+0928><U+093F><U+092F><U+092E> <U+0968><U+0966><U+0966><U+096B>: <U+0905><U+0928><U+0941><U+0915><U+094D><U+0930><U+092E><U+0923><U+093F><U+0915><U+093E> | first=Department of Information Technology and Electronics | trans_title = Right to Information Act 2005: Index | url = http://infotech.up.nic.in/hindi/suchana/suchana.htm | accessdate = June 25, 2011 | language=Hindi}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Home | url = http://www.jrhu.com/index.htm | accessdate = June 24, 2011 | publisher=Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = E-Governance in India: initiatives & issues | last=Sinha | first=R. P. | publisher=Concept Publishing Company | date=December 1, 2006 | location=New Delhi, India | isbn=8180693112, 9788180693113 | page=104}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = Handbook of universities | last1=Gupta | first1=Amita | last2=Kumar | first2=Ashish | publisher=Atlantic Publishers and Distributors | date=July 6, 2006 | location=New Delhi, India | isbn=8126906081, 9788126906086 | page=395}}</ref> The act appointed Jagadguru Rambhadracharya as the life-long chancellor of the university. The university offers graduate, post-graduate and doctorate degrees in various streams including Sanskrit, Hindi, English, Sociology, Psychology, Music, Drawing and Painting, Fine Arts, Special Education, Education, History, Culture & Archeology, Computer & Information Sciences, Vocational Education, Law, Economics, and [[Prosthetics]] and [[Orthotics]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Courses Offered | url = http://www.jrhu.com/index_files/Page449.htm | accessdate = April 25, 2011 | publisher=Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University}}</ref> The university plans to start offering courses in [[Ayurveda]] and [[Medical Sciences]] from 2013.<ref name="amar-ujala">{{cite news | last=Correspondent | first=Mahoba | date=July 6, 2011 | title = <U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0902><U+0917><U+094B><U+0902> <U+0915><U+0947> <U+0932><U+093F><U+090F> <U+092E><U+0947><U+0921><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932> <U+0915><U+093E><U+0932><U+0947><U+091C> <U+091C><U+0932><U+094D><U+0926> | url = http://www.amarujala.com/city/Mahoba/Mahoba-33757-44.html | accessdate =July 9, 2011 | publisher=Amar Ujala | trans_title=Soon, a medical college for the disabled | language=Hindi}}</ref> Admissions are restricted to the four types of disabled students&nbsp;<U+2013> visually impaired, hearing impaired, mobility impaired and mentally impaired, as defined by the Disability Act (1995) of the [[Government of India]]. As per the Government of Uttar Pradesh, the university is among the chief educational institutes for Information Technology and Electronics in the state.<ref>{{cite web | last=Government of Uttar Pradesh  | first=Department of Information Technology and Electronics | title = <U+0915><U+092E><U+094D><U+092A><U+094D><U+092F><U+0942><U+091F><U+0930> <U+0936><U+093F><U+0915><U+094D><U+0937><U+093E> | url = http://infotech.up.nic.in/hindi/ourgoal/our_goal_3.htm | accessdate = June 24, 2011 | language=Hindi | trans_title=Computer Education}}</ref> 354 disabled students were awarded various degrees in the second convocation of the university held in March 2010.<ref>{{cite news | last=Correspondent | first=Chitrakut | publisher=Jagran Yahoo | title = <U+0935><U+093F><U+0915><U+0932><U+093E><U+0902><U+0917> <U+0935><U+093F><U+0936><U+094D><U+0935><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F> <U+0915><U+093E> <U+0926><U+0942><U+0938><U+0930><U+093E> <U+0926><U+0940><U+0915><U+094D><U+0937><U+093E><U+0924> <U+0938><U+092E><U+093E><U+0930><U+094B><U+0939> <U+096D> <U+092E><U+093E><U+0930><U+094D><U+091A> <U+0915><U+094B> | url = http://in.jagran.yahoo.com/news/local/uttarpradesh/4_1_6211271.html | date = February 24, 2010 | accessdate=July 2, 2011 | language=Hindi | trans_title=Second convocation of the Handicapped University to be held on March 7}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | publisher=Bundelkhand Live | language=Hindi | title = <U+0914><U+092A><U+091A><U+093E><U+0930><U+093F><U+0915><U+0924><U+093E><U+0913><U+0902> <U+0915><U+0947> <U+092C><U+0940><U+091A> <U+0938><U+0902><U+092A><U+0928><U+