==Memorandum of understanding==

JRHU had signed a [[Memorandum of understanding]] with five institutions, which are [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Allahabad]]; Sri Sadguru Seva Trust, Chitrakuta; Department of Cerbral Palsy at [[Nizam's Institute of Medical Sciences]], Hyderabad; Department of Psychology at [[Allahabad University]] and National Institute for Visually Handicapped, Dehradun.<ref name="jrhu-presentation"/><ref name="jrhu"/>

==Notable Visitors==

Many notable visitors has visited JRHU. Some of them are former Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh [[Rajnath Singh]], Member of [[Rajya Sabha]] [[Murli Manohar Joshi]], Chairman of [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]] Arun Nigvekar, former Union minister [[Uma Bharati]], General secretary of [[Association of Indian Universities|AIU]] Dayanand Donagaokar, former Chief justice of [[Allahabad High Court]] Hemant Laxman Gokhale, former Vice Chancellor of [[University of Kashmir]] Abdul Wahid, sitting judge of the [[Supreme Court of India]] [[Markandey Katju]], justice of the Supreme Court of India [[Dalveer Bhandari]], justice of the Allahabad high court Mr.Singh, former Major-General Ian Cardozo.<ref name="jrhu-presentation"/>

==Support from other Organizations==

The creation of the university was highly supported by the [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]].<ref name="disabilityindia">{{cite web | title = Jagatguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University | url = http://www.disabilityindia.org/djinstjuly05C.cfm#up | accessdate = August 29, 2011 | publisher=Disability India Network}}</ref> The University also receives support from UGC.<ref name="jansatta" /> The registrar of the university, Avanish Chandra Mishra, said that they received help from [[Rehabilitation Council of India]] for running courses in Information Technology, Teacher Training Programme, Fine Art, Music etc.<ref name="goswamitulsidasji"/> The University has been declared eligible to receive central assistance under section 12(b) of UGC Act 1956.<ref name="ngoboards"/>

==Other Features==
[[File:JRHU - Students Hall of Residence.jpg|thumb|Students Hall of Residence]]
;Placement Center

To assist its students in selecting appropriate courses/programmes and getting placements based on their performances, the University has its own placement center. The Centre also arranges capsule training programmes to help youths for proper rehabilitation.<ref name="goswamitulsidasji">{{cite web | title = Jagadguru Rambhadracharya Handicapped University, Chitrakoot, U.P., India | url = https://sites.google.com/site/goswamitulsidasji/jagadguru-rambhadracharya-handicapped-university | accessdate = August 29, 2011 | publisher=Shri Tulsi Peeth Seva Nyas}}</ref>

;Distance Education
In order to reach out to students with limited mobility, the University offers distance education programmes which are also recognised by The Distance Education Council, [[IGNOU]], New Delhi and wide its letter no. F.No./DEC/Recog./JRBHU/2006/1434 Dated 31/07/2006, it has recognized following programmes, currently offered by the university in distance mode, through its various centres. Like other program of the University, this programme is open only for persons with disabilities.<ref name="jrhu"/><ref name="DEC">{{cite web | title = Distance Education Centre (Recognized by DEC, IGNOU New Delhi) | url = http://www.jrhu.com/index_files/Page370.htm | accessdate = August 29, 2011 | publisher=Shri Tulsi Peeth Seva Nyas}}</ref>

